Dear Tamar and Adam

I hope you are both well.

We have received the first trades for both investment accounts last week an=
d this week.
All went well.

There are a couple of things I wanted to briefly discuss with you if possib=
le. Would you have time for a call this week?


1.       Both managers have sent orders for certain bonds that can only be =
traded by professional clients.

Currently, the entire relationship is classified as a Retail relationship -=
 in terms of Client classification.

Since the managers act in a professional capacity and meet the minimum stan=
dards required to be opted up to a Professional Classification, the IBI an =
YL accounts could be 'opted up' should you wish to do so. This would then a=
llow the managers to trade these bonds.

An opt-up would be particularly for these accounts, without affecting your =
personal Retail classification.

Should you wish to proceed with this, we can send you the required form for=
 you to sign.
Yes, let's get this set up.

 2.       During our phone call on 24 September, I explained that we can ha=
ve income generated by the YL and IBI automatically redirected into respect=
ive income accounts. This because of the different tax treatments in case o=
f potential remittance - Capital Gains @ 20pct versus Income @ 45%.

Have you had the chance to think about this? Now that the accounts have equ=
ities and bonds, income could start coming any time.
I think this would require a short discussion with the trading team, to see=
 if it impacts their flow. I'll get back to you.
 3.       I have been asked by IBI to confirm that all is properly set up i=
n terms of fees etc.

Since unfortunately I was not a part of the discussions regarding the inves=
tment account openings, I just wanted to briefly discuss your understanding.
I'm not sure this was discussed very deeply. I personally don't recall the =
rates we were quoted, but would be happy to discuss.

All the best,

Adam

